text: Saint-Dizier-Masbaraud is a commune in the Creuse department in central France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint-Dizier-Leyrenne (the seat) and Masbaraud-Mérignat.Arrêté préfectoral 3 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Creuse department ==References== Category:Communes of Creuse
title: Saint-Dizier-Masbaraud
